16 “(b) Moneys other than revenues from the 9-8-8 coordinated crisis services
17 tax that are deposited into the fund shall be used for:
18 “(A) A wide array of crisis stabilization services, including services pro-
19 vided by:
20 “(i) Crisis stabilization centers;
21 “(ii) Facilities offering short-term respite services;
22 “(iii) Peer respite centers; and
23 “(iv) Behavioral health urgent care walk-in centers; and
24 “(B) Community mental health program provision of crisis stabilization
25 services or funding to cities to establish or maintain one or more mobile
