1 rupted. A drug-dependent person may be physically dependent, a condition in
2 which the body requires a continuing supply of a drug or controlled substance
3 to avoid characteristic withdrawal symptoms, or psychologically dependent, a
4 condition characterized by an overwhelming mental desire for continued use
5 of a drug or controlled substance.]
6 “[(5)] (4) ‘Halfway house’ means a publicly or privately operated profit
